In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 27, 2015, as Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day. He honors the sacrifices of fallen heroes and recognizes the Gold Star Mothers and Families who carry forward their memories. The President acknowledges the support and love provided by parents, spouses, children, siblings, and friends of service members. He expresses gratitude for the sacrifices made by these families and encourages government officials and the American people to display the flag and hold appropriate ceremonies to show gratitude and respect for Gold Star Mothers and Families.